File: South Africa is taking part in a research trial to find treatment for the COVID-19. JOHANNESBURG -  Confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa have risen to 10,015, according to Health Minister Zweli Mkhize. Mkhize delivered the latest updated information in a statement on Sunday night. COVID-19: NCC taking heat, decisions to be challenged Eight new fatalities were reported by the minister, bringing the death toll to 194. More than 4,000 people have recovered from the virus in the country. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.